# u-forge.ai Project Structure Guide

Local-first TTRPG worldbuilding tool with AI-powered knowledge graphs. Built in Rust.

**Status:** Early prototype. CLI demo only. Phases 1 + 2 complete. Hardware re-architecture complete (inter-phase). LLM queuing + reranking infrastructure added (Phase 4 partial). sqlite-vec complete. Next: axum server (Phase 3).

## Architecture Overview

Read [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md) for full details (module map, SQLite schema, resolved bugs, design decisions).
Read [migration.md](mdc:migration.md) for the phased migration plan and current completion status.

## Current Architecture

- **Facade**: [src/lib.rs](mdc:src/lib.rs) — `KnowledgeGraph` struct (owns storage + schemas) + `ObjectBuilder`
- **Storage**: [src/storage.rs](mdc:src/storage.rs) — SQLite via `rusqlite` (bundled). Tables: `nodes`, `edges`, `chunks`, `schemas` + FTS5 virtual table `chunks_fts` + sqlite-vec virtual table `chunks_vec` (768-dim cosine ANN). Key constants: `EMBEDDING_DIMENSIONS = 768`, `MAX_CHUNK_TOKENS = 350`, `ENABLE_HIGH_QUALITY_EMBEDDING = false`. `KnowledgeGraphStorage` is the only storage struct.
- **Embeddings**: [src/embeddings.rs](mdc:src/embeddings.rs) — `EmbeddingProvider` trait + `LemonadeProvider` (HTTP) + `EmbeddingManager`. FastEmbed/ORT/ONNX have been removed. Transcription types have been moved to `src/transcription.rs`; they are re-exported from `embeddings.rs` for backward compatibility.
- **Transcription**: [src/transcription.rs](mdc:src/transcription.rs) — `TranscriptionProvider` trait + `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` + `TranscriptionManager` + `mime_for_filename()`. Split out of `embeddings.rs` so embedding and transcription can evolve independently and be routed to different hardware.
- **Hardware Abstraction**: [src/hardware/mod.rs](mdc:src/hardware/mod.rs) — `DeviceCapability` enum, `HardwareBackend` enum, `DeviceWorker` trait. Sub-modules:
  - [src/hardware/npu.rs](mdc:src/hardware/npu.rs) — `NpuDevice` (embedding + STT + **LLM** on AMD NPU via FLM; no GPU contention). `NpuDevice::new()` takes a 4th `llm_model: Option<&str>` arg. `NpuDevice::from_registry()` auto-discovers all three capabilities. `NpuDevice::llm_only()` is synchronous. `pub chat: Option<LemonadeChatProvider>` field (no `GpuResourceManager` — NPU is independent).
  - [src/hardware/gpu.rs](mdc:src/hardware/gpu.rs) — `GpuDevice` (STT + LLM on AMD GPU via ROCm; shares `GpuResourceManager`)
  - [src/hardware/cpu.rs](mdc:src/hardware/cpu.rs) — `CpuDevice` (TTS via Kokoro on host CPU)
- **Inference Queue**: [src/inference_queue.rs](mdc:src/inference_queue.rs) — `InferenceQueue` + `InferenceQueueBuilder` + `QueueStats`. Unified MPMC capability-based dispatch queue. Five capability channels:
  - `embed_queue` → NPU embedding workers
  - `transcribe_queue` → NPU FLM whisper + GPU whispercpp workers compete (first-free wins)
  - `synthesize_queue` → CPU Kokoro TTS workers
  - `generate_queue` → NPU FLM LLM + GPU llamacpp workers compete (first-free wins). **Now wired** — the previous `// NOTE:` bypass comment has been removed.
  - `rerank_queue` → `LemonadeRerankProvider` workers
  - Public methods: `embed`, `embed_many`, `transcribe`, `synthesize`, `generate`, `ask` (convenience), `rerank`. Builder gains `with_reranker(LemonadeRerankProvider)`. Builder also gains `with_embedding_provider(Arc<dyn EmbeddingProvider>, name)` for standalone llamacpp/CPU/ROCm workers. Per-job retry: up to 3 attempts with exponential backoff in `run_embed_worker`.
- **Extended Lemonade Integration**: [src/lemonade.rs](mdc:src/lemonade.rs) — `LemonadeModelRegistry`, `GpuResourceManager`, `LemonadeTtsProvider`, `LemonadeSttProvider`, `LemonadeChatProvider`, `LemonadeStack`, **`LemonadeRerankProvider`**, **`SystemInfo`**, **`LemonadeCapabilities`**. GPU resource management for STT/LLM contention. `LemonadeChatProvider.gpu` is now `Option<Arc<GpuResourceManager>>` — `None` for NPU-backed providers (no locking needed), `Some(gpu)` for GPU-backed providers.
- **Full-Text Search**: `search_chunks_fts(query, limit)` — SQLite FTS5, keyword/phrase/prefix matching. **Semantic Search**: `search_chunks_semantic(query_embedding, limit)` — sqlite-vec vec0 cosine ANN, returns `(ChunkId, ObjectId, String, f32)` tuples. Both live in `storage.rs` / `lib.rs`; Phase 4 will combine them in `search_hybrid()`.
- **Vector Search**: `src/vector_search.rs` **has been deleted**. ANN search is now provided by sqlite-vec: `chunks_vec` vec0 virtual table in `storage.rs`, `upsert_chunk_embedding()` and `search_chunks_semantic()` on both `KnowledgeGraphStorage` and `KnowledgeGraph`.
- **Schemas**: [src/schema.rs](mdc:src/schema.rs) + [src/schema_manager.rs](mdc:src/schema_manager.rs) + [src/schema_ingestion.rs](mdc:src/schema_ingestion.rs)
- **Data Import**: [src/data_ingestion.rs](mdc:src/data_ingestion.rs) — JSONL two-pass import. BUG-6 (dedup) and BUG-7 (cross-session edge resolution) are fixed.
- **Embedding Queue**: [src/embedding_queue.rs](mdc:src/embedding_queue.rs) — embedding-only async background worker. Superseded for new work by `InferenceQueue`; retained for callers that need per-request status tracking.

## Migration Direction

**Current state:** SQLite + FTS5, Lemonade embeddings, hardware abstraction, unified inference queue, `LemonadeRerankProvider`, and `cli_demo` FTS5→rerank pipeline are all complete. All nine tracked bugs resolved.

- ✅ **sqlite-vec** — ANN vector search complete (`chunks_vec` vec0, 768-dim cosine, `search_chunks_semantic`)
- ⏳ **Phase 3** — `axum` HTTP/WebSocket server for web UI
- ⏳ **Phase 4 (pipeline)** — Wire reranking into `KnowledgeGraph` hybrid search (FTS5 + vec + rerank); streaming LLM responses
- ⏳ **Phase 5** — Cargo workspace split

**Standard on [Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade)** (AMD, OpenAI-compatible API) for all AI:
- Embeddings: `POST /api/v1/embeddings` (implemented — `LemonadeProvider` in `embeddings.rs`)
- Transcription: `POST /api/v1/audio/transcriptions` (implemented — `LemonadeTranscriptionProvider` in `transcription.rs` for NPU/simple use; `LemonadeSttProvider` in `lemonade.rs` for GPU-managed use)
- Reranking: `POST /api/v1/reranking` (**implemented** — `LemonadeRerankProvider` in `lemonade.rs`; wired into `InferenceQueue` via `rerank_queue`)
- Chat/LLM: `POST /api/v1/chat/completions` (**fully queued** — `LemonadeChatProvider` in `lemonade.rs`; dispatched via `generate_queue` for both GPU llamacpp and NPU FLM models)
- System info: `GET /system-info` (**implemented** — `SystemInfo::fetch()` in `lemonade.rs`; derives `LemonadeCapabilities` from installed recipe backends)

**Linux hardware capability mapping** (derived from `/system-info`):

| Hardware | Recipes/Backends | Capabilities |
|---|---|---|
| AMD NPU (XDNA2) | FLM | `Embedding`, `Transcription` (NpuStt), `TextGeneration` (NpuLlm) |
| AMD iGPU (ROCm/Vulkan) | llamacpp:rocm, llamacpp:vulkan, whispercpp:vulkan | `Transcription` (GpuStt), `TextGeneration` (GpuLlm), `Reranking` |
| CPU | kokoro | `TextToSpeech` |

## Key Integration Points

The `EmbeddingProvider` trait in [src/embeddings.rs](mdc:src/embeddings.rs) is the primary abstraction for embedding work. Only `LemonadeProvider` currently implements it. Do NOT bypass the trait.

The `TranscriptionProvider` trait in [src/transcription.rs](mdc:src/transcription.rs) is the primary abstraction for STT work. Do NOT bypass the trait.

The `DeviceWorker` trait in [src/hardware/mod.rs](mdc:src/hardware/mod.rs) is the abstraction for physical compute devices. New hardware backends must implement it.

For new code that needs embedding, transcription, TTS, LLM generation, or reranking: use `InferenceQueueBuilder` to wire up devices and obtain an `InferenceQueue`. Do not call provider HTTP clients directly from business logic.

`LemonadeChatProvider.gpu` is `Option<Arc<GpuResourceManager>>`. Always pass `Some(gpu)` for GPU-backed llamacpp models so they respect the GPU serialisation lock. Pass `None` (or use `new_npu()` / `from_registry_npu()`) for NPU FLM models — they run on dedicated silicon with no shared resource.

`KnowledgeGraph` does **not** hold an `EmbeddingManager` or `InferenceQueue`. Storage and schema operations are fully synchronous and require no running server. All AI capabilities are opt-in — construct them separately when needed.

## Integration Test Threading

Integration tests hit a shared live Lemonade Server. When `LEMONADE_URL` is set,
all modules' integration tests run concurrently by default, causing intermittent
GPU/NPU resource contention on the server side.

**Always run the full test suite with `--test-threads=1` when `LEMONADE_URL` is set.**
`dev.sh` sets this flag automatically when it detects `LEMONADE_URL` in the environment.

```bash
# Correct — single-threaded to avoid server contention
LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1 cargo test -- --test-threads=1

# dev.sh handles this automatically
export LEMONADE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1
./dev.sh --backend-only
```

